    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Dealer_Lifecycle</fullName>
        <canEscalate>true</canEscalate>
        <description>Updates the status of a test drive booking as the rep moves the customer through the visit — arrived, drive started, drive ended, no-show, cancelled.</description>
        <developerName>Dealer_Lifecycle</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Identify the booking first by calling Get Bookings with daysAhead=0 and dealerAccountId=001bm00001iMVjFAAW, then match by customer name. The output contains each booking as &quot;[bookingId=&lt;id&gt;] &lt;name&gt; | ...&quot;. Extract the value after bookingId= (a Salesforce record Id starting with a0) — NEVER pass the TR-#### as bookingId. If multiple bookings match the same name today, ask the rep to disambiguate by time or vehicle model.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Map rep phrases to newStatus: arrived, checked in, or is here map to Arrived. Start drive, starting, or going out map to In Progress. Finished, end drive, we are back, or done map to Completed. No show or did not come map to No-Show. Cancelled or they cancelled map to Cancelled.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After Update Status returns, relay the statusMessage verbatim. If newStatus was Arrived, add: &quot;Customer receives a welcome email automatically.&quot; If Completed, add: &quot;Ready to capture the outcome when you are.&quot;</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
