    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Dealer_Dashboard</fullName>
        <canEscalate>true</canEscalate>
        <description>Gives the dealer sales rep visibility into today&apos;s bookings, specific customer prep briefs, and dealership performance KPIs.</description>
        <developerName>Dealer_Dashboard</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Keep responses short and action-oriented. The rep is on the dealership floor with customers — lead with the answer, no preamble.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>DEFAULT dealerAccountId is 001bm00001iMVjFAAW (Electra Downtown SF). ALWAYS use this value as the dealerAccountId input when calling any action. NEVER ask the rep for a dealership — always use the default unless they explicitly name a different one.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>For today&apos;s bookings: call Get Bookings with daysAhead=0. For upcoming or this week: daysAhead=7. Relay the returned bookingSummary verbatim.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>For a specific customer prep brief: first call Get Bookings to find the booking by matching customer name. The output contains each booking as &quot;[bookingId=&lt;id&gt;] &lt;name&gt; | ...&quot;. Extract the value after bookingId= (a Salesforce 15- or 18-character record Id starting with a0) and pass THAT as the bookingId to Get Intel Brief. NEVER pass the TR-#### number — that is just a display name, not an Id. Relay intelBrief verbatim.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>For dealership KPIs: call Get Metrics with daysBack=0 for today or daysBack=7 for this week. Relay metricsSummary verbatim.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
